    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Separate treatises on a particular subject, typically written expositions of a subject narrow enough in scope to exclude all but a single aspect of the subject, for example, a study of the works of a single artist. In book cataloging, non-serial bibliographic items complete in one part or in a finite number of separate parts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
